  "answer": "In *Manusmṛti* chapter 1, Manu provides the etymology for 'Nārāyaṇa' (a name of the creator deity) at verse 1.10: the waters (*nārāḥ*) are the \"sons of Nara,\" and since they were his first \"dwelling place\" (*ayana*), he is called Nārāyaṇa.[^1]\n\n[^1]: *Manusmṛti*, [Chapter 1, paragraph p-0bfa5b](/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/01/translation/#p-0bfa5b).",
